The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Twenty20 world meet venues confirmed

A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) Tuesday confirmed details of the venues for next years inaugural ICC Twenty20 World Championships in South Africa, according to a release. 

The three venues chosen for the event, which will take place in September 2007, are Kingsmead in Durban, Wanderers in Johannesburg and Newlands, Cape Town. 

The tournament will involve 12 teams, the 10 ICC Full Members and the two top Associates. 

Botha cleared 

South Africa off-spinner Johan Botha can resume playing at international level after remodeling his action. 

The ICC said Tuesday that Botha had done remedial work on his action with the Cricket South Africa since being suspended on February 7, a day after making his Test debut in Australia. 

The ICC lifted the suspension after approving an independent reassessment of his action. Botha had been called for excessive levels of straightening in both his off-break and doosra deliveries. 




